A senior education researcher is leading a four-year longitudinal study of a complex educational intervention rolled out across about 80 schools in 12 districts, with student-level outcomes measured annually and teacher-level survey data collected at intervals. The analytic complexity demands a serious design and analysis companion app. The study has the structure of students nested in classrooms in schools in districts, with the intervention assigned at the school level over staggered timing — a setting that requires careful integration of multilevel models, panel data methods, and quasi-experimental research design. Build a professional analytic companion app where the researcher articulates the formal analytic plan and pre-registers it before unblinding analyses. The app walks the researcher through specifying the levels of the data hierarchy and which variables sit at which level, choosing between hierarchical linear modeling specifications with random effects models at school and district levels versus fixed effects estimators for school, defending the choice on substantive and statistical grounds. The researcher specifies the primary outcome, the secondary outcomes, and the planned heterogeneity analysis using interaction terms — does the intervention work differently for students who entered with lower baseline achievement, in schools with higher teacher turnover, in districts with stronger implementation support? Mixed methods research design integration is supported: the researcher describes how the qualitative coding schemes from teacher and principal interviews will be analyzed alongside the regression analysis, and how findings will be triangulated. Model diagnostics are pre-specified — what residual patterns would trigger a re-specification, what sensitivity analyses will probe the parallel-trends assumption underlying the quasi-experimental difference-in-differences comparison. The app produces a complete pre-analysis plan suitable for posting to a public registry, with the full multilevel models specification, the planned interaction terms, the robustness checks, and the threshold for declaring the intervention's effect statistically and practically meaningful. Every analytic decision is logged so the analysis is defensible to funders, journal reviewers, and the participating districts.